{"id":500642,"url":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aharon_Lichtenstein","text":"e=\"preserve\">Aharon Lichtenstein (23 May 1933 \u2013 20 April 2015) was a French-born American-Israeli Orthodox rabbi, rosh yeshiva and writer. He was an authority of Jewish law (\"Halacha\"). He won the Israel Prize in 2014.\nLichtenstein was born in Paris and grew up in New York, United States. He studied at Yeshiva University and Harvard University. He married in 1960 and had six children.\nLichtenstein died on 20 April 2015 in Jerusalem, aged 81.","categories":[],"infobox_types":[],"annotations":[{"uri":"French_people","surface_form":"French","offset":69},{"uri":"Americans","surface_form":"American","offset":81},{"uri":"Israel","surface_form":"Israel","offset":90},{"uri":"Orthodox_Judaism","surface_form":"Orthodox","offset":98},{"uri":"Rabbi","surface_form":"rabbi","offset":107},{"uri":"Rosh_yeshiva","surface_form":"rosh yeshiva","offset":114},{"uri":"Writer","surface_form":"writer","offset":131},{"uri":"Jewish_law","surface_form":"Jewish law","offset":162},{"uri":"Israel_Prize","surface_form":"Israel Prize","offset":197},{"uri":"Paris","surface_form":"Paris","offset":244},{"uri":"New_York","surface_form":"New York","offset":265},{"uri":"United_States","surface_form":"United States","offset":275},{"uri":"Yeshiva_University","surface_form":"Yeshiva University","offset":304},{"uri":"Harvard_University","surface_form":"Harvard University","offset":327},{"uri":"Jerusalem","surface_form":"Jerusalem","offset":426}]}